My code basically computes all directed, open night tours on a 5x5 chessboard using a recursive backtracking algorithm. So, over here our Knight's tour is a sequence all the knight's moves that visits every single square exactly once, where our tors are open(which means that the final square does not connect back to the starting) and directed (which means that the reversed paths are treated as distinct solutions). In the end , my program basically prints out each tour as an array of the square number in the order in which they were visited. 